  "title": "Senior Cybersecurity Consultant (Malware Analysis)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Cyber Threat Intelligence</strong><br /><strong>Digital Forensics</strong><br /><br /><strong>Role</strong><br />The incumbent will analyze and investigate malwares, advanced persistent threats (APTs), and other cyber threats, contributing to the overall mission of protecting Singapore’s cyberspace and enhancing our nation’s cybersecurity posture.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform in-depth analysis of <strong>malwares</strong> to understand the behaviour and capabilities of a malware and prepare comprehensive reports on malware analysis findings to present the findings to both technical and non-technical stakeholders alike.</li><li>Provide expertise in dissecting malware with crucial insights, immediate and actionable intelligence needed to understand, contain and prevent cyberattacks.</li><li>Conduct in-depth research with more systematic understanding of evolving malware threats and create high fidelity detection mechanisms to identify emerging threats.</li><li>Oversee the implementation of new projects and technologies, by translating plans into operations through well-defined workflows, automation and robust technical solutions.</li><li>Act as a subject matter expert (SME) for the malware analysis function within the team.</li><li>Develop and deliver training programmes on advanced malware analysis techniques.</li><li>Mentor and provide technical guidance to junior malware analysts, fostering their growth and skill development.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Background in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or related field</li><li>At least 5 years of relevant working experience with domain expertise in <strong>Malware Analysis</strong></li><li>Possess <strong>Malware Analysis</strong> or other relevant <strong>cybersecurity</strong> certifications is an advantage</li></ul>",
